landing+docs: fix legally-risky claims on competitors, put DoorDash next to Mise

Audit of competitor pages (veryfi.com, klippa.com) surfaced three
claims we could not back up with the primary source:

1. Veryfi "$500/mo min" — their site advertises a free trial and lists
   no public pricing. Removed the specific figure; now says
   "commercial — free trial, paid plans on request".

2. Klippa "100+ languages" — false. Their FAQ currently states they
   support Latin-alphabet languages and names 11 (English, Dutch,
   Norwegian, Danish, Swedish, Finnish, Italian, Portuguese, Spanish,
   German, French), with others "on request". Updated to match.

3. Klippa "ISO + GDPR certified" — not stated on their current product
   page (they say "Secure, Compliant, Hosted in EU"). Replaced with
   the verified "Hosted in EU" phrasing.

Also updated the Klippa brand to "Klippa (now Doxis)" — their site
has rebranded, and the old name is what integrators still search for.

Grid order changed: DoorDash now sits in the column next to Mise
instead of at the far right. DoorDash is the strongest conceptual
peer, so the visual comparison should be Mise-vs-DoorDash first,
with commercial APIs trailing.

Backend: no code changes. Frontend: vite build clean.
